
This is the README file for p4est.
p4est is free software licensed under GPL version 2 (or later).

p4est is a C library to manage a collection (a forest) of multiple
connected adaptive quadtrees or octrees in parallel.

See more documentation in the doc subdirectory.

Version 0.3.0 handles both 2D and 3D forests.

Version 0.2.0 includes libsc 0.5.0.  It handles the 2D forest.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

Example configure lines:

# GNU compilers, debug, default BLAS from libsc (not used by p4est).
# Using an external libsc installed under SC_PATH.
#
configure \
        CFLAGS="-Wall -Wextra -Wshadow -Wno-unused-parameter \
                -O0 -g -rdynamic" \
        --enable-debug --enable-mpi --with-sc=<SC_PATH>

# Intel compilers, debug, mpi, no builtin zlib.
# Default BLAS, VTK ASCII double output.
#
configure \
        CFLAGS="-Wall -w2 -Wcheck -O0 -g -rdynamic -wd869,981" \
        --enable-debug --enable-mpi --without-zlib \
        --disable-vtk-binary --enable-vtk-doubles
